name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the clinical study.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the clinical study.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the clinical study.

documentedBy.name: documentedBy
documentedBy.definition: A USDM relationship between the Study and StudyDefinitionDocument classes signifying that the study is documented in a study definition document.

versions.name: versions
versions.definition: A USDM relationship between the Study and StudyVersion classes which identifies the set of versions associated with the study.

text.name: text
text.definition: An instance of structured text that represents the study identifier.

scope.name: scope
scope.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyIdentifier and Organization classes which provides the details associated with each organization that has assigned the study identifier.

identifierScheme.name: identifierScheme
identifierScheme.definition: The name of the organization that provides the identifier for the entity.

identifier.name: identifier
identifier.definition: A unique symbol that establishes identity of the organization. (BRIDG)

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the organization.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the organization.

type.name: type
type.definition: A characterization or classification of the formalized group of persons or other organizations collected together for a common purpose (such as administrative, legal, political) and the infrastructure to carry out that purpose.

legalAddress.name: legalAddress
legalAddress.definition: A USDM relationship between the Organization and Address classes which provides the legal address for an organization.

managedSites.name: managedSites
managedSites.definition: A USDM relationship between the Organization and StudySite classes which identifies the set of study sites managed by the organization.

studyCells.name: studyCells
studyCells.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyCell classes which identifies the set of study cells associated with the study design.

indications.name: indications
indications.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and Indication classes which identifies the set of indications associated with the study design.

studyInterventions.name: studyInterventions
studyInterventions.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyIntervention classes which identifies the set of study interventions associated with study design.

estimands.name: estimands
estimands.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and Estimand classes which identifies the set of estimands associated with the study design.

objectives.name: objectives
objectives.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and Objective classes which identifies the set of objectives associated with the study design.

population.name: population
population.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyDesignPopulation classes which identifies the population associated with the study design.

encounters.name: encounters
encounters.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and Encounter classes which identifies the set of encounters associated with the study design.

scheduleOfActivities.name: scheduleOfActivities
scheduleOfActivities.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and ScheduleOfActivities classes which identifies the set of schedules of activities associated with the study design.

epochs.name: epochs
epochs.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyEpoch classes which identifies the set of study epochs associated with the study design.

arms.name: arms
arms.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyArm classes which identifies the set of study arms associated with the study design.

elements.name: elements
elements.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyElement classes which identifies the set of study elements associated with the study design.

documentVersions.name: documentVersions
documentVersions.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and StudyDefinitionDocumentVersion classes which identifies the version of the study definition documents associated with the study design.

activities.name: activities
activities.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and Activity classes which identifies the set of activities associated with the study design.

biospecimenRetentions.name: biospecimenRetentions
biospecimenRetentions.definition: A USDM relationship between the StudyDesign and BiospecimenRetention classes which identifies the status of biospecimen retentions related to the study design.

notes.name: notes
notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the study design.

therapeuticAreas.name: therapeuticAreas
therapeuticAreas.definition: A categorization of a disease, disorder, or other condition based on common characteristics and often associated with a medical specialty focusing on research and development of specific therapeutic interventions for the purpose of treatment and prevention.

characteristics.name: characteristics
characteristics.definition: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspect of a study design.

studyType.name: studyType
studyType.definition: The nature of the investigation for which study information is being collected. (After clinicaltrials.gov)

studyPhase.name: studyPhase
studyPhase.definition: A step in the clinical research and development of a therapy from initial clinical trials to post-approval studies. NOTE: Clinical trials are generally categorized into four (sometimes five) phases. A therapeutic intervention may be evaluated in two or more phases simultaneously in different trials, and some trials may overlap two different phases. [21 CFR section 312.21; After ICH Topic E8 NOTE FOR GUIDANCE ON GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS FOR CLINICAL TRIALS, CPMP/ICH/291/95 March 1998]

name.name: name

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the study design.

rationale.name: rationale
rationale.definition: Reason(s) for choosing the study design. This may include reasons for the choice of control or comparator, as well as the scientific rationale for the study design.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the study design.

codes.name: codes
codes.definition: A short sequence of characters that represents the disease/condition indication.

notes.name: notes

plannedEnrollmentNumberRange.definition: The range of values representing the planned number of subjects to be entered in a clinical trial, within the study design population.

plannedEnrollmentNumberQuantity.name: plannedEnrollmentNumberQuantity

minValue.name: minValue
minValue.definition: The smallest value in quantity or degree in a set of values.

maxValue.name: maxValue
maxValue.definition: The largest value in quantity or degree in a set of values.

isApproximate.name: isApproximate
isApproximate.definition: An indication as to whether the value range is almost, but not quite, exact.

text.name: text
text.definition: An instance of unstructured text that represents the study title.

type.name: type
type.definition: A characterization or classification of the study title.

text.name: text
text.definition: An instance of unstructured text that represents how the masking is performed and maintained.

isMasked.name: isMasked
isMasked.definition: An indication as to whether the study role is masked.

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the study site.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the study site.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the study site.

country.name: country
country.definition: The country in which the study site is located.

text.name: text
text.definition: An instance of unstructured text that represents the study amendment impact.

isSubstantial.name: isSubstantial
isSubstantial.definition: An indication as to whether the study amendment's impact on the study is substantial.

type.name: type
type.definition: A characterization or classification of the study amendment impact.

notes.name: notes
notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the study amendment impact.

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the medical device.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the medical device.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the medical device.

hardwareVersion.name: hardwareVersion
hardwareVersion.definition: A form or variant of hardware; one of a sequence of copies of the physical components from which a computer is constructed, each incorporating new modifications.

softwareVersion.name: softwareVersion
softwareVersion.definition: A form or variant of software; one of a sequence of copies of a software program, each incorporating new modifications. (NCI)

embeddedProduct.name: embeddedProduct
embeddedProduct.definition: A USDM relationship between the MedicalDevice and AdministrableProduct classes which identifies the administrable product that is an integral component of the medical device.

identifiers.name: identifiers
identifiers.definition: A USDM relationship between the MedicalDevice and MedicalDeviceIdentifier classes which provides the set of identifiers related to the medical device.

notes.name: notes
notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the medical device.

sourcing.name: sourcing
sourcing.definition: An indication as to whether the medical device is obtained from a local or central source.

text.name: text
text.definition: An instance of structured text that represents the medical device identifier.

type.name: type
type.definition: A characterization or classification of the medical device identifier.

scope.name: scope
scope.definition: A USDM relationship between the MedicalDeviceIdentifier and Organization classes which provides the details associated with each organization that has assigned the identifier.

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the product organization role.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the product organization role.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the product organization role.

code.name: code
code.definition: A symbol or combination of symbols which is assigned to the product organization role.

appliesTo.name: appliesTo
appliesTo.definition: A USDM relationship between the ProductOrganizationRole and either the AdministrableProduct or MedicalDevice class that identifies the administrable product or medical device to which the product organization role applies.

organization.name: organization
organization.definition: A USDM relationship between the ProductOrganizationRole and Organization classes which identifies the organization associated with the product organization role.

blindingSchema.name: blindingSchema
blindingSchema.definition: The type of experimental design used to describe the level of awareness of the study subjects and/ or study personnel as it relates to the respective intervention(s) or assessments being observed, received or administered.

intentTypes.name: intentTypes
intentTypes.definition: The planned purpose of the therapy, device, or agent under study in the clinical trial.

model.name: model
model.definition: The general design of the strategy for assigning interventions to subjects in a clinical study. (clinicaltrials.gov)

subTypes.name: subTypes
subTypes.definition: The nature of the interventional study for which information is being collected.

studyPhase.name: studyPhase
studyPhase.definition: The study phase associated with the interventional study design.

studyType.name: studyType
studyType.definition: The study type associated with the interventional study design.

characteristics.name: characteristics
characteristics.definition: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspects of an interventional study design.

therapeuticAreas.name: therapeuticAreas
therapeuticAreas.definition: A categorization of a disease, disorder, or other condition based on common characteristics and often associated with a medical specialty focusing on research and development of specific therapeutic interventions for the purpose of treatment and prevention, which is associated with the interventional study design.

notes.name: notes
notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the interventional study design.

name.name: name

description.name: description

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the interventional study design.

rationale.name: rationale
rationale.definition: Reason(s) for choosing the interventional study design. This may include reasons for the choice of control or comparator, as well as the scientific rationale for the study design.

studyCells.name: studyCells
studyCells.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and StudyCell classes which identifies the set of study cells associated with the interventional study design.

indications.name: indications
indications.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and Indication classes which identifies the set of indications associated with the interventional study design.

studyInterventions.name: studyInterventions

encounters.name: encounters

activities.name: activities

scheduleTimelines.name: scheduleTimelines

epochs.name: epochs
epochs.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and StudyEpoch classes which identifies the set of study epochs associated with the interventional study design.

arms.name: arms
arms.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and StudyArm classes which identifies the set of study arms associated with the interventional study design.

elements.name: elements
elements.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and StudyElement classes which identifies the set of study elements associated with the interventional study design.

documentVersions.name: documentVersions

model.name: model
